  "text": "The LLVM optimization pass pipeline lifecycle follows this execution chain:\n\n1. **PassBuilder** (llvm/include/llvm/Passes/PassBuilder.h:114): The PassBuilder class is the primary entry point for constructing pass pipelines. It provides methods like `buildModuleOptimizationPipeline(OptimizationLevel Level, ThinOrFullLTOPhase LTOPhase)` (declared at line 249-250) that orchestrate the assembly of default pipelines.\n\n2. **PassBuilderPipelines** (llvm/lib/Passes/PassBuilderPipelines.cpp): This file implements the pipeline assembly logic. The `buildModuleOptimizationPipeline` function (starting at line 1477) constructs the module-level optimization pipeline by creating a ModulePassManager and adding passes to it in the appropriate order. This function reads the optimization level and constructs different pipelines for O0, O1, O2, O3, Oz, Os, etc.\n\n3. **PassRegistry.def** (llvm/lib/Passes/PassRegistry.def): This critical registry file defines how each pass is instantiated through macro definitions. It contains entries like `FUNCTION_PASS(\"dse\", DSEPass())` that specify the mapping from pass names to their constructors. The file is #included multiple times in PassBuilder.cpp with different macro definitions to enable different processing (e.g., registering passes by name, registering analyses, building pass instances).\n\n4. **PassManager Template** (llvm/include/llvm/IR/PassManager.h:159-226): The core pass execution engine is implemented as a template class `PassManager<IRUnitT, AnalysisManagerT, ExtraArgTs...>`. The `run()` method (line 190-191) is the execution method that runs all contained passes sequentially over the provided IR unit, calling each pass's run method and managing analysis invalidation based on PreservedAnalyses returned by each pass.\n\n5. **DeadStoreElimination** (llvm/lib/Transforms/Scalar/DeadStoreElimination.cpp and header): As a concrete example of a pass in the pipeline, the DSEPass class (defined in llvm/include/llvm/Transforms/Scalar/DeadStoreElimination.h:28) implements the `run(Function &F, FunctionAnalysisManager &FAM)` method. When invoked by PassManager, it performs dead store elimination on the function IR.\n\nThe complete flow: PassBuilder constructs a ModulePassManager containing FunctionPassManagers (and other nested managers), which themselves contain individual function passes like DSEPass. When PassManager::run() is called on the top-level manager, it recursively invokes all nested passes, with each pass executing over its designated IR unit (Module, Function, Loop, etc.) and registering its analysis results with the corresponding AnalysisManager for use by subsequent passes."
}

